  <source>Office of Rare Diseases (ORD)</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      OBJECTIVES: I. Characterize the nutritional and metabolic profile of children and adolescents&#xD;
      with epidermolysis bullosa.&#xD;
&#xD;
      II. Determine patterns of body composition in these patients. III. Determine the energy&#xD;
      requirements of these patients by measuring resting energy expenditure.&#xD;
&#xD;
      IV. Assess protein nutrition by measuring lean body mass.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      PROTOCOL OUTLINE:&#xD;
&#xD;
      Data collected from a 5-day food diary are analyzed for protein, nutrient, and calorie&#xD;
      intake. Nutritional, metabolic, and body composition are evaluated by indirect calorimetry,&#xD;
      total body electrical conductivity, total body potassium, and lean body mass.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
